  "detailedRequirements": "<h2><span style=\"font-family:trebuchet ms; font-size:17.333333333333332px\">Overview</span></h2>\n&nbsp;\n\n<p><span style=\"font-family:arial; font-size:14.666666666666666px\">Welcome to the Backend #2 challenge for our Mobile Hybrid buildpack project. There will be several challenges in this project dealing both with a nodejs based backend hosted on Heroku and an Ionic front end demo application. Get involved now and follow along!</span></p>\n&nbsp;\n\n<p><span style=\"font-family:arial; font-size:14.666666666666666px\">Before starting, please read </span><a href=\"https://github.com/topcoderinc/BP-Ionic-Heroku/blob/dev/Backend/docs/MobileHybridIonicHerokuBuildpack.pdf\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\"><u>MobileHybridIonicHerokuBuildpack.pdf</u></a><span style=\"font-family:arial; font-size:14.666666666666666px\">. This document explains the overall concept were trying to achieve.</span></p>\n&nbsp;\n\n<h2><span style=\"font-family:trebuchet ms; font-size:17.333333333333332px\">Challenge Goal</span></h2>\n&nbsp;\n\n<p><span style=\"font-family:arial; font-size:14.666666666666666px\">In this challenge we want to add an additional module to our backend to implement email sending. The use case for a module like this is when applications need send status or notification types of emails. It&#39;s not intended to be an email client.</span></p>\n&nbsp;\n\n<p><span style=\"font-family:arial; font-size:14.666666666666666px\">We have a solid backend base that is well organized and modular - thanks to, well.. thanks to YOU (the community). It is very important that you follow the established structure of the backend and implement this as a module following the same pattern as the CRUD module and the additional sample module.</span></p>\n&nbsp;\n\n<h2><span style=\"font-family:trebuchet ms; font-size:17.333333333333332px\">Details</span></h2>\n&nbsp;\n\n<p><span style=\"font-family:arial; font-size:14.666666666666666px\">- This implementation must implement </span><a href=\"https://github.com/topcoderinc/BP-Ionic-Heroku/blob/dev/Backend/api/emailApi.yaml\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\"><u>the email API</u></a><span style=\"font-family:arial; font-size:14.666666666666666px\"> using Mailgun (you can sign-up for a free account)</span></p>\n&nbsp;\n\n<p><span style=\"font-family:arial; font-size:14.666666666666666px\">- Auth should just be basic for now, see how it&#39;s implemented in the CRUD module and mirror that setup. All endpoints should auth.</span></p>\n&nbsp;\n\n<p><span style=\"font-family:arial; font-size:14.666666666666666px\">- The API may not 100% match the capabilities of Mailgun, but most (if not all) features we should be able to implement. If we need changes to the API, please discuss in the forums - do not modify it without prior discussion.</span></p>\n&nbsp;\n\n<p><span style=\"font-family:arial; font-size:14.666666666666666px\">- To reiterate, the primary intent is *sending* email - it&#39;s not a service for receiving email. The GET request types are primarily for getting the </span><em>status</em><span style=\"font-family:arial; font-size:14.666666666666666px\"> of an email which has been sent (you&#39;ll need the Mailgun </span><a href=\"https://documentation.mailgun.com/user_manual.html#tracking-messages\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\"><u>event and tracking features</u></a><span style=\"font-family:arial; font-size:14.666666666666666px\"> for this).</span></p>\n&nbsp;\n\n<p><span style=\"font-family:arial; font-size:14.666666666666666px\">- All config variables should be coded to pull from the Heroku env with fallback to local definitions if not present on the Heroku instance. Use the </span><em>config</em><span style=\"font-family:arial; font-size:14.666666666666666px\"> npm module already present in the codebase for this.</span></p>\n&nbsp;\n\n<p><span style=\"font-family:arial; font-size:14.666666666666666px\">- Inline documentation is critical, this is a &quot;reference project&quot; so should be well documented and everything should be clear.</span></p>\n&nbsp;\n\n<h2><span style=\"font-family:trebuchet ms; font-size:17.333333333333332px\">Working with the Code Base</span></h2>\n<br />\n<span style=\"font-family:arial; font-size:14.666666666666666px\">Clone </span><a href=\"https://github.com/topcoderinc/BP-Ionic-Heroku\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\"><u>the repo</u></a><span style=\"font-family:arial; font-size:14.666666666666666px\"> from Github and create a local branch for this challenge. When complete, commit your changes locally and then zip the whole thing up for your submission. We&#39;ll soon be working directly out of Github once the front-end is going.</span>",
